🍴 NikiTreats – A Food Website

NikiTreats is a static website built with HTML and CSS.
It represents a fictional food brand showcasing a menu, an about section, and a clean design suitable for small restaurants, food bloggers, or culinary portfolios.
This project was created as a beginner-friendly web development project to practice structuring websites, applying CSS for design, and deploying projects to GitHub Pages.

✨ Features
Attractive Banner – A large banner image showcasing food.
About Section – Brief description about NikiTreats, its purpose, and philosophy.
Menu Section – Display of dishes with images, names, and an “Order Now” button.
Responsive Layout – Works on desktop and adapts to different screen sizes.
Interactive Buttons – Buttons change color on hover.
Footer Section – Includes quick links (Contact, Privacy, FAQ).

📂 Project Structure
Here’s how the files are organized:

NikiTreats/
│── index.html          # Main HTML file (structure of the website)
│── style.css           # CSS file (styling of the website)
│── img/                # Folder for images
│    ├── banner-junkfod.jfif
│    ├── MargheritaPizza.jpg
│    ├── SpaghettiCarbonara.jpg
│    ├── CaesarSalad.jpg
│    └── ChocolateLavaCake.jfif
│── README.md           # Documentation file

🛠️ Technologies Used
HTML5 – for structuring content.
CSS3 – for styling, layout, and hover effects.

💻 How to Use / Run Locally
If you want to run this project on your local computer:

Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/zodenikita/NikiTreats.git

Navigate to the folder
cd NikiTreats

Open index.html in your browser
Just double-click index.html or right-click → "Open with Browser".

🌐 How to Deploy on GitHub Pages
To make this website live:
Push all files to your GitHub repository.

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit - NikiTreats Website"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/zodenikita/NikiTreats.git
git push -u origin main

Go to your repository on GitHub.
Click on Settings → Pages.
Under Source, select:
Branch: main
Folder: /root
Click Save.

Your website will be live at:
https://zodenikita.github.io/NikiTreats/

📸 Preview of Sections
Header – Site name styled with a bold background.
Banner – Wide food image across the page.
About Section – Text explaining the purpose of NikiTreats.
Menu Section – Food cards with images, dish names, and buttons.
Footer – Simple footer with navigation links and copyright.

